From what I have understand, .Net Core 2.0 is the implementation of .Net Standard 2.0 .
However I'm facing an issue when I'm trying to move my code from a .Net Core 2.0 project to .Net Standard 2.0 with the following message :
> No overload for method 'Replace' takes 3 arguments

.Net Standard 2.0 references the following methods : 
 - System.String.Replace(String, String);
 - System.String.Replace(char, char);
https://docs.microsoft.com/fr-fr/dotnet/api/?view=netstandard-2.0&term=string.replace

In another side, .Net Core 2.0 references the following methods :
 - System.String.Replace(String, String, bool, CultureInfo);
 - System.String.Replace(String, String, StringComparison);
 - System.String.Replace(String, String);
 - System.String.Replace(char, char);
https://docs.microsoft.com/fr-fr/dotnet/api/?view=netcore-2.0&term=string.replace

Is it possible to add these missing definitions to the next version of .NetStandard ?

